VAR, which made its debut at the 2018 World Cup in Russia, will now be deployed for the women’s tournament which kicks off in June in France. MIAMI - Video assistant referee (VAR) will be used at this year’s women’s World Cup, Fifa confirmed on Friday. VAR, which made its debut at the 2018 World Cup in Russia, will now be deployed for the women’s tournament which kicks off in June in France. The decision was confirmed at a meeting of Fifa’s Council in Miami.